    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2834</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-28T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 29, 4.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4279. From many signs there are indications that Germany is contemplating a
                    return to reckless submarine war. People like <persName corresp="#p_BE1"
                        >Bassermann</persName>, leader of National Liberals, and Gutmann, Director
                    of Dresdner Bank, who formerly opposed, now favor it. There is a tendency to
                    stir up feeling against America as a first step. I do not think this question
                    will become acute until after our elections, and possibly not until spring, when
                    Germany will have great number of submarine boats with trained crews. Am
                    informed that one shipyard alone is turning out over two submarine boats per
                    week.</p>
                <p>Newspapers publish ridiculous statements about attitude of President and America.
                    For instance, one paper large circulation, printing <pb facs="0572" n="286"
                        xml:id="pg_286"/> pleasant comments of American papers on arrival <hi
                        rend="italic">Deutschland</hi> concludes: “Only the semiofficial <hi
                        rend="italic">Evening Post</hi> keeps silent.”</p>
                <p>Possibly entrance Roumania to-day may accentuate submarine situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
